gypsy day
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the day that sharemilkers move herds, usually on foot, and belongings from one farm property to another (usually June 1)
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: DB notes: 'gypsy days' plural is more correct in Waikato and Taranaki - they often start around May 29
